{"name":"Survivalist's Pouch","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.CwQMykmCzMU59TZd"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Survivalist's Pouch","_id":"sf3fshktUf0fbSWg","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<ul><li><p>Bedroll</p></li><li><p>Two-Person Tent</p></li><li><p>Tinderbox</p></li><li><p>Mess Kit</p></li><li><p>250 Feet of Rope</p></li><li><p>Grappling Hook</p></li><li><p>10 Foot Pole</p></li><li><p>10 Foot Ladder</p></li><li><p>Crowbar</p></li><li><p>Sledgehammer</p></li><li><p>Miner's Pick</p></li><li><p>Hammer</p></li><li><p>20 Pitons</p></li><li><p>20 Iron Spikes</p></li><li><p>Shovel</p></li><li><p>Portable Ram</p></li><li><p>Block and Tackle</p></li><li><p>Lantern</p></li><li><p>5 Flasks of Oil</p></li><li><p>2 Sets of Clothing</p></li><li><p>Snowshoes</p></li><li><p>20 Rations</p></li><li><p>5 Waterskins</p></li><li><p>Iron Pot</p></li><li><p>Rain Catcher</p></li><li><p>Fishing Tackle</p></li><li><p>Tools (Artisan's, Kits, etc.)</p></li><li><p>5 Containers of Ammunition</p></li><li><p>2 Pouches with up to 500 coins each</p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671572860348,"modifiedTime":1675988538250,"lastModifiedBy":"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW"},"_id":"CwQMykmCzMU59TZd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Supremacy Ammo Types","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.QpkaM3tPITowCNCa"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Supremacy Ammo Types","_id":"8W2AsH4QqsGXETkT","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h3>Tier 1 - 25 gold</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deadly</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 Bonus to Attack and Damage rolls.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Elemental Payload</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Choose Fire, Cold, Lightning, Acid, or Poison, each piece of ammunition deals an additional 1d4 damage of the chosen element.</span></p><h3>Tier 2 - 75 gold</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Devastating</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +2 bonus to Attack and Damage rolls.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Elementally Infused</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Choose Fire, Cold, Lightning, Acid, or Poison, each piece of ammunition deals an additional 1d8 damage of the chosen element.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Pummeling</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This ammunition deals Bludgeoning damage instead of Piercing. A creature hit with this ammunition must make Strength Saving Throw against your Weapon DC or fall prone. Concentration checks made as a result of damage from this ammunition are made at disadvantage.</span></p><h3>Tier 3 - 250 gold</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Cataclysmic</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Gain a +3 Bonus to Attack and Damage rolls.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Blunderbuss </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This ammunition taps in to the use of an extradimensional space to deliver a larger payload than should be possible. When you fire a piece of Blunderbuss ammunition, your weapon discharges a 20-foot Cone of Shrapnel instead of a single projectile. Make a ranged attack roll with your weapon at each target in the cone, dealing 4d12 damage on a successful hit.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671573977385,"modifiedTime":1675988538251,"lastModifiedBy":"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW"},"_id":"QpkaM3tPITowCNCa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Supremacy, Fusil of Retaliation","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.XqUAJNbYu6dgFyPN"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Supremacy, Fusil of Retaliation","_id":"YPeZLBwNKuWwWl9F","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Enhanced Sights</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have upgraded the sights on the rifle. Your short and long range are both doubled with this weapon.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Ammo Smithing</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">ve learned to craft your own bullets efficiently. With one hour</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s work you can craft 10 basic bullets provided you have access to suitable scrap materials.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Canister Bombs</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have learned to craft crude explosives that will detonate on impact. With ten minute</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s work and 50 gold worth of materials you can craft one of the following types of bombs: <strong>Poison, Blaze, Shrapnel</strong>.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">You have a bandolier which can hold 5 canister bombs. You can draw and throw a bomb in place of any attack you make. Thrown canister bombs have a range of 15 feet. Storing canister bombs anywhere other than your bandolier can be extremely hazardous.</span></p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.QpkaM3tPITowCNCa]{Supremacy Ammo Types}</p><p>@UUID[JournalEntry.YtuJcCCKZKPjRMTe]{Canister Bombs}</p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 Bonus to Attack and Damage rolls made with this weapon.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Targeting Guidance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You can tap in to embedded magic within the weapon to enhance your aim. You gain the ability to cast the Hunter</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s Mark spell at 1</span><sup><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">st</span></sup><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> level. You can use this ability a number of times equal to half your Proficiency Bonus rounded up. You regain all uses at the end of a long rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Arcane Ammo Smithing</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">ve learned to infuse magic in to ammunition you craft. By using 25 gold worth of materials, you can craft one of the following types of ammunition instead of basic ammunition: <strong>Deadly, Elemental Payload</strong></span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Canister Launcher</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> A launching tube is attached to the bottom of your rifle to allow you to launch canister bombs a decent distance. Instead of throwing a canister, you can load it in to the launcher and fire it. Launched canisters have a range of 40 feet.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Canister Bombs</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have learned to craft more potent versions of your canister bombs using 100 gold worth of materials: <strong>Mephitic Poison, Conflagration, Fragmentation</strong>.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +2 bonus to Attack and Damage rolls with this weapon.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Expert Arcane Ammo Smith</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have developed improved ways of binding magic to ammunition. With 75 gold worth of materials, you can craft one of the following types of ammunition instead of basic ammunition: <strong>Devastating, Elemental Infused, Pummeling</strong>.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Master Ammo Smith</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have become even more efficient at crafting your own ammunition. You can now craft 20 pieces of ammunition with the time and resources it would normally take to craft 10.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Enhanced Rifling</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Upgrades to the barrel of the weapon allow for more accurate shots that penetrate deeper. The base damage of the weapon increases to <strong>2d12 Piercing</strong>.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Efficient Launching</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Launched Canisters now have a range of 60 feet.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deadly Cannisters</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have devised even deadlier cannister bombs using 500 gold worth of materials: <strong>Virulent Poison, Inferno, Fulminating</strong>.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Greater Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +3 bonus to Attack and Damage rolls made with this weapon.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Master Arcane Ammo Smith</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">You have learned to craft the following types of ammunition using 250 gold worth of materials: <strong>Cataclysmic, Blunderbuss</strong></span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671573681398,"modifiedTime":1675988538254,"lastModifiedBy":"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW"},"_id":"XqUAJNbYu6dgFyPN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Canister Bombs","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.YtuJcCCKZKPjRMTe"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Canister Bombs","_id":"ZVgsdyyhzHbQUDaX","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h3>Tier 1 - 50 gold - Thrown - 15 feet</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Poison</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases gas in a 10-foot radius sphere. Each creature in the sphere must make a Constitution saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 3d8 Poison Damage and is Poisoned. On a success a creature takes half damage and is not Poisoned. A Poisoned creature can repeat the save at the end of each of its turns.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Blaze </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact creates a 5-foot cube of fire that persists for 5 rounds. Any creature that enters the flames for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there takes 2d4 fire damage.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Shrapnel </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases a concussive wave filled with flying debris. Each creature within a 10-foot radius of the point of impact must make a Dexterity saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 3d6 Piercing Damage and any movement speed it has is halved until the end of its next turn. On a success a creature takes half damage and no other effect.</span></p><h3>Tier 2 - 100 gold - Launched - 40 Feet</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Mephitic Poison</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases concentrated gas in a 10-foot radius sphere. Each creature in the sphere must make a Constitution saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 5d8 Poison Damage and is Poisoned. On a success a creature takes half damage and is not Poisoned. A Poisoned creature can spend an action to attempt to shake off the poison by repeating the saving throw.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Conflagration </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact creates a 10-foot cube of roaring fire that persists for 5 rounds. Any creature that enters the flames for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there takes 2d8 fire damage.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Fragmentation </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases a concussive wave filled with flying debris. Each creature within a 15-foot radius of the point of impact must make a Dexterity saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 6d6 Piercing Damage and any movement speed it has is halved until the end of its next turn. On a success a creature takes half damage and no other effect.</span></p><h3>Tier 3 - 500 gold - Lofted - 60 Feet</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Virulent Poison</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases concentrated gas in a 15-foot radius sphere. Each creature in the sphere must make a Constitution saving throw against your Weapon DC with Disadvantage. On a failure the creature takes 8d8 Poison Damage and is Poisoned. On a success a creature takes half damage and is not Poisoned. A Poisoned creature can spend an action to attempt to shake off the poison by repeating the saving throw with Disadvantage.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Inferno </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact creates a 15-foot cube of raging fire that persists for 5 rounds. Any creature that enters the flames for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there takes 3d12 fire damage.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Fulminating </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases a concussive wave filled with flying debris. Each creature within a 20-foot radius of the point of impact must make a Dexterity saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 6d6 Piercing Damage and 4d6 Thunder Damage and any movement speed it has is halved until the end of its next turn. On a success a creature takes half damage and no other effect.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671574126208,"modifiedTime":1675988538255,"lastModifiedBy":"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW"},"_id":"YtuJcCCKZKPjRMTe","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Kivi's Symbiote","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Kivi's Symbiote","type":"text","_id":"V7pzccWKQLxFwy1m","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Flavor Text</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Temperament. </strong>TBD</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Equipment. </strong>A symbiotic lifeform that lives within the body</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Awakening Phrase. </strong>TBD</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>True Awakening Durability.</strong> N/A</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Toll. </strong>You suffer two levels of exhaustion and lose all benefits of the symbiote until you finish a long rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Base Traits</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Hammerfists.</strong> Your fists are especially punishing. Whenever you make an unarmed attack using your fists, you roll 2 of your Martial Arts dice.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Manifest Barbs</strong>. As a bonus action, you can manifest a number of barbed spines equal to a roll of your Martial Arts Die + your Proficiency Bonus. These barbs can then be launched with a range of 60 feet in place of any unarmed attack you would make. They do not benefit from Hammerfists. When you Manifest Barbs any remaining barbs from previous manifestations are first reabsorbed in to your body. While you have Barbs Manifested, you have Advantage on Charisma (Intimidation) Ability Checks.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Awakening</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">When you Awaken your symbiote, it begins to take more direct control. [[TODO: List physical characteristics and changes and whatnot]].</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">You gain access to a pool of Mutation points to fuel various abilities over the course of the Awakening. The capacity of this pool is equal to your Monk level, and upon Awakening it contains points equal to half your Monk level + your Constitution modifier. As part of the action to Awaken the symbiote you can spend 3 Mutation Points to also activate the Rapid Reflexes mutation.</span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Gaining Points</strong> – Whenever you reduce a creature to 0 hitpoints with an unarmed attack you can absorb some of its essence to fuel your mutations. You add Mutation Points to your pool depending on the creature’s size:</span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">1 Point for a Tiny or Small creature</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">2 Points for a Medium creature</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">3 Points for a Large creature</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">4 Points for a Huge creature</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">5 Points for a Gargantuan or Larger creature.</span></p></li></ul></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Upkeep</strong> – Certain Mutation abilities require a continual upkeep of energy in addition to the up-front cost to trigger the effect. Upkeep is accomplished as a Free Action at the start of your turn. You can end a mutation at any time as a Free Action.</span></p></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Variable Enhancement</strong> (2 Mutation Points, 1 point Upkeep) Pick one Simic Hybrid Animal Enhancement you do not already have. You have the benefits of that enhancement while this mutation is active.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Rapid Reflexes.</strong> (Bonus Action, 3 Mutation Points, 1 point Upkeep) You gain a +2 bonus to Armor Class and Advantage on Dexterity Saving Throws while this mutation is active.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Rapid Growth Barbs.</strong> (Free Action, 1 Mutation Point) You use Manifest Barbs once.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Heavy Barbs</strong> (Free Action, 1 Mutation Point, 1 point Upkeep) Your Barbs benefit from Hammerfists while this mutation is active.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Regeneration.</strong> (4 Mutation Points) As an Action, you regain 2d6 + Monk Level + Constitution Mod hitpoints.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Snap Out Of It.</strong> (2 Mutation Points) Once per turn as a Free Action you can gain Advantage on a Saving Throw to end an ongoing condition.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>I Can Take It.</strong> (2 Mutation Points) When you take damage, you can use your Reaction to reduce the damage by an amount equal to 1d6 + Monk Level + Constitution Mod</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">True Awakening</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">When you Truly Awaken the Symbiote, you fully relinquish control temporarily. [[TODO: List Physical Changes.]] You gain a Mutation Pool with a capacity of 2x your Monk level, but you must pay an upkeep of 1 Point at the start of each turn, even if you have no active mutations. If you have 0 points remaining in your pool after paying Upkeep at the start of your turn, True Awakening ends and you suffer the Toll.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Brutal Hammerfist.</strong> (Bonus Action, 3 Mutation Points, 2 point Upkeep, Mutually Exclusive with Vorpal Fists) Your speed is halved and attacks with your fists deal maximum damage while this mutation is active.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Vorpal Fists.</strong> (Bonus Action, Variable, Mutually Exclusive with Brutal Hammerfists) You hone your fists into extremely deadly weapons, causing effects based on the number of Mutation Points you spend according to the following chart (effects are cumulative, spending more points gets you that effect as well as every previous effect):</span></p><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"1\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-yfti-tbllook:1184;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><tbody><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Initial Cost</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Upkeep</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Effect</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:1\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">3</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">2</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Your Critical Hit Range is reduced by 2</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:2\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">4</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">3</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">You do an additional 2d10 damage on Critical Hits</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:3\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">5</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">4</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Your Critical Hit Range is reduced by 4</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:4;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">6</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">5</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">You do an additional 4d10 damage on Critical Hits</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong> </strong></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Power Slam</strong>. (Action, 6 Mutation Points) Slam both fists in to the ground, causing a shockwave to radiate out. Each creature within 20 feet of you must make a Dexterity Saving Throw, suffering 8d10 Bludgeoning damage on a failed save, or half as much on a successful one. This damage can be modified by your Dragon Strike feature.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Fists of Fury.</strong> (Action, 6 Mutation Points) Move up to your speed, making as many attacks as possible while satisfying the following conditions: You must move at least 5 feet after making an attack, you must move in a direction that takes you further away from your starting position.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Barb Frenzy.</strong> (Action, 2 Mutation Points per creature targeted) You rapidly manifest and launch barbs at multiple creatures in range. Pick any number of creatures within 60 feet of you. For each creature, roll 1d4 and launch that many barb attacks at it. Once you use this ability, you can’t use it or Manifest Barbs again until the end of your Next Turn.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.dlRZPB0yfFmL3WbJ"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675987936855,"modifiedTime":1675988538272,"lastModifiedBy":"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW"},"_id":"dlRZPB0yfFmL3WbJ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Indensian Warden's Staff","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.itJSYwIXuCdef687"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Indensian Warden's Staff","_id":"YPeZLBwNKuWwWl9F","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">The staff of an Indensian Warden is as much a badge of honor and pride as it is a deadly weapon. Only those who prove their dedication to standing as the first line in the watch are awarded the rank of Warden and the weapon that goes with it.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Aetheric Flow</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This weapon can be used as a focus for casting spells.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Clawed Hand</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Sharpened claws have been added to the grasping hand at the end of the staff. Melee attacks with the staff now deal an additional 1d4 slashing damage.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Warden Spirit</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The staff is imbued with a force of magic that functions as a Warden Spirit. You can call upon the spirit 4 times per day.</span></p><ul><li><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Empowering your Spirit</strong><br />Warden Spirits thrive on seeking out potential threats and ending them before they can become too great. At the DM</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s discretion, ending a threat of sufficient significance can permanently empower the spirit, increasing the number of times you can call on it per day by 1. It may also be possible to undertake specific quests for the explicit purpose of strengthening your spirit.</span></p></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Retaliation</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When a creature within 5 feet of you makes an attack against a target other than you, you can use your reaction to call upon the Warden Spirit to make an Opportunity Attack against the triggering creature.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Potency</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 Bonus to Weapon and Spell Attack and Damage rolls and the save DC of spells cast using the staff as a focus.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Aggression</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Once per turn when you hit a target with this staff you can use a free action to call upon your Warden Spirit to empower the strike. If you do, the attack deals an additional 2d6 force damage.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Compassion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Any spell you cast that restores hitpoints heals for an additional 1d4.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Sharpened Claws</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus slashing damage provided by Clawed Hand increases to 1d6.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Strength of Spirit</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You can call upon your Warden Spirit an additional 2 times per day.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Enhanced Potency</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus provided by your Spirit of Potency increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Unchecked Aggression</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus damage dealt by your Spirit of Aggression increases to 3d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Welling Compassion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus healing provided by your Spirit of Compassion increases to 1d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Advanced Retaliation</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Spirit of Retaliation can now be used when you are hit with an attack by a creature within 5 feet of you.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Razor Claws</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">The bonus slashing damage provided by Clawed Hand increases to 1d8.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Strength of Spirit</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You can call upon your Warden Spirit an additional 2 times per day.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Heightened Potency</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus provided by your Spirit of Potency increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Unbridled Aggression</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus damage provided by your Spirit of Aggression increases to 4d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Boundless Compassion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus healing provided by your Spirit of Compassion increases to 1d8.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Tenacity</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> While wielding this staff you can take one additional reaction each round, provided you are able to take reactions.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Overwhelming Force</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When you take the attack action on your turn, prior to rolling the attack, you can use a free action to draw upon your Warden Spirit more fully than usual. By permanently reducing the maximum number of times you can call upon your Warden Spirit per day by 1 you can treat the number rolled on the die as a 20. Once you call upon the spirit in this way you can</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t do so again until you finish a long rest.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false,"type":"text"}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671573681398,"modifiedTime":1675988538258,"lastModifiedBy":"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW"},"_id":"itJSYwIXuCdef687","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Indensian Battle Plate of the Guardian","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.pVX6WLkRn2iZ4TEv"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Indensian Battle Plate of the Guardian","_id":"YPeZLBwNKuWwWl9F","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Cleverly Designed Fittings</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Particular care has been paid to ensuring this armor is as easy to put on as possible. You can don this armor unassisted in one minute. If you have the aid of two other capable creatures, the armor can be donned as an action.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Quick Release Buckles</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When you want out of your armor, you usually want out sooner rather than later. These buckles make that possible, allowing you to doff it as an action.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Guardian Spirit</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The armor is imbued with a force of magic that functions as a Guardian Spirit. You can call upon the spirit 4 times per day.</span></p><ul><li><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Empowering your Guardian Spirit</strong><br />Guardian Spirits are driven onwards by acts of heroism, bravery, and sacrifice in service to others. At the DM</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s discretion, an act of sufficient significance can permanently empower the spirit, increasing the number of times you can call on it per day by 1. It may also be possible to undertake specific quests for the explicit purpose of strengthening your spirit.</span></p></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Resilience</strong> - When you suffer a critical hit, you can use your reaction to call upon your Guardian Spirit to bolster your defenses, granting you resistance to all damage from the triggering attack.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Vigilance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> While wearing this armor you can</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t be surprised and enemies gain no benefit from being unseen when attacking you.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Urgency</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> As a free action you can call upon your Guardian Spirit to assist you in putting on your armor, allowing you to don it as an action.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Strength of Spirit</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You can call upon your Guardian Spirit an additional 2 times per day.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Protection</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 bonus to Armor Class and Saving Throws while wearing this armor.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Stubbornness</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> While wearing this armor, you have advantage on death saving throws.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Focus</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When you cast a spell requiring concentration with a range of Self or that includes you as a target you can use a free action to call upon your Guardian Spirit for assistance. If you do, the spirit maintains concentration on the spell for the duration. You can have the spirit break concentration as a free action.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Strength of Spirit</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You can call upon your Guardian Spirit an additional 2 times per day.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Unparalleled Protection</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from your Spirit of Protection increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spirit of Death</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>’</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>s Defiance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When you are reduced to 0 hitpoints but not killed outright, you can call upon your Guardian Spirit to try and save you. Roll 1d20 and consult the following chart. Prior to rolling, you can choose to draw upon the spirit more fully. By permanently reducing the maximum number of times you can call upon your Guardian Spirit per day by 1 you can treat the number rolled on the die as a 20. Once you call upon the spirit in this way you can</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t do so again until you finish a long rest.</span></p><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"1\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-yfti-tbllook:1184;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><tbody><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes\"><td style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">1-4</span></p></td><td style=\"width:472.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">The spirit is unable to assist you.</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:1\"><td style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">5-9</span></p></td><td style=\"width:472.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">The spirit heals you for 2d8 + your Constitution modifier.</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:2\"><td style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">10-14</span></p></td><td style=\"width:472.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">The spirit heals you for 4d8 + Twice your Constitution modifier.</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:3\"><td style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">15-19</span></p></td><td style=\"width:472.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">The spirit heals you for half your total hitpoints and you gain resistance to all damage until the start of your next turn.</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:4;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes\"><td style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">20</span></p></td><td style=\"width:472.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">The spirit manifests in its full glory. You regain all your hitpoints, are cured of any negative conditions or ongoing effects, and can immediately take a full turn in combat. After this turn ends, initiative order resumes as normal.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false,"type":"text"}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671573681398,"modifiedTime":1675988538262,"lastModifiedBy":"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW"},"_id":"pVX6WLkRn2iZ4TEv","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Nightfall, Ferocity of the Moonwalker","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Nightfall, Ferocity of the Moonwalker","type":"text","_id":"FSWmI40OZNTietvP","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Initial Item</span></h2><h4><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Great Club</span></h4><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Damage</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> 1d10 Bludgeoning</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Two-Handed, Heavy, Martial Weapon, Primal Weapon</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Primal Weapon </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Attacks with a Primal Weapon can be made using Wisdom, rather than Strength or Dexterity.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Aetheric Flow</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This weapon can be used as a focus for casting spells.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Warpriest Techniques</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have a pool of technique points equal to your proficiency modifier + 2. You regain all spent points at the end of a short rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deflective Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as an Action. You gain a +2 bonus to AC while wielding the club in both hands until you take a Short or Long Rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Hemorrhaging Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as an Action. Make a melee attack against a creature. On a hit, the creature takes 1d6 damage at the start of each of its turns for 3 rounds.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Puissance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 bonus to Attack rolls, Damage rolls, and the Save DC of spells made with the club.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Focused Mind Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as a Bonus Action. The next healing spell you cast on this turn also ends 1 Frightened or Charmed condition on the target.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Gnarled Branch </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The base damage of the club increases to 2d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Rapid Reflexes</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from your Deflective Technique increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Reliable Hemorrhaging</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Hemorrhaging Technique is now Reliable. If you miss with the attack after using the technique, the technique point is refunded.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Concussive Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as a Free Action after hitting with a melee attack. The target of the attack must make a Constitution saving throw against your Spell DC. On a failure, the target is stunned until the start of your next turn. If the attack was a Critical Hit, the target automatically fails this save. Succeed or Fail, the target then becomes immune to this technique until the end of your next turn.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Puissance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Puissance increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Rapid Focus</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Focused Mind Technique is now a Free Action.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Path of Twilight Flames Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as an action. Cold flames spring up about your hooves for one minute. While these flames exist, your hooves deal an additional 1d8 radiant damage and whenever you move you leave behind a patch of radiant fire until the flames around your hooves dissipate. When creatures of your choice enter the fire for the first time on a turn or start their turn there, they take 1d8 radiant damage.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Petrified Branch</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The base damage of the club increases to 3d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deep Hemorrhaging</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The damage from your Hemorrhaging Technique increases to 2d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Vigilant Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as a free action when you use Vigilant Blessing, causing it to apply to a number of creatures equal to your proficiency bonus.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical Enhancements</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Greater Puissance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Puissance increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Twilight Inferno</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The damage dealt by your Path of Twilight Flames increases to 2d8.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Wings of Twilight Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as a free action when you use Steps of Night, causing it to target a number of creatures equal to your Proficiency Bonus.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.s4xyrfTblr0QvFpO"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673412750379,"modifiedTime":1675988538266,"lastModifiedBy":"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW"},"_id":"s4xyrfTblr0QvFpO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
